==English==
===Noun===
'''impurity''' (''plural'' impurities)
# The condition of being [[impure]]; because of [[contamination]], [[pollution]], [[adulteration]] or [[insufficient]] [[purification]]
#: ''Even [[animal]]s in the [[Jewish]] system cause '''impurity''' only when they are dead.''
# A [[component]] or [[additive]] that [[render]]s something else impure
#: ''The '''impurities''' in the [[iron]] [[ore]] made extraction of the iron very difficult.''
# A state of [[immorality]] or [[sin]]
#: ''With his [[cheat]]ing, [[lie|lying]] and [[steal]]ing, he epitomised the '''impurity''' of humanity''
